#id=1
#text=Before you plant a tree , you must contact the utility company .
#id=2
#text=They will come to your property and mark out utility lines .
#id=3
#text=Without doing this , you may dig down and hit a line , which can be lethal !
#id=4
#text=Once you know where to dig , select what type of tree you want .
#id=5
#text=Take things into consideration such as how much sun it gets , what zone you are in , and how quickly you want it to grow .
#id=6
#text=Dig a hole large enough for the tree and roots .
#id=7
#text=Place the tree in the hole and then fill the hole back up with dirt .
#id=8
#text=Many small trees will need support until they are bigger .
#id=9
#text=This will ensure they grow tall and straight .
#text=It is crucial to keep the tree watered !
#text=It will need a lot of water at first .
#text=Mulch is helpful to keep the soil moist .
#text=It 's also important to wait until the threat of a frost has passed or is not in the near future .
#text=Giving care to your new tree will ensure that it will grow big and strong !
